description: TEHRAN - The Iranian contingent walked out in the Parade of Nations at Paris Olympics opening ceremony Friday evening.
title: Iran lights up Parade of Nations at Paris Olympics

description: TEHRAN - In the current multipolar world, there may not be a region as unstable as MENA.
title: MENA and the unstable balance of the world of politics

description: TEHRAN- On Friday, Cong Peiwu, the ambassador of the People's Republic of China in Tehran, announced the upcoming departure of a high-level Chinese delegation to Iran for the inauguration ceremony of President-elect Masoud Pezeshkian.
title: Chinese delegation to deliver crucial message to Pezeshkian: Chinese envoy

description: TEHRAN – Rafael Grossi, Director General of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), has extended his congratulations to Iran's newly elected President, Masoud Pezeshkian, and expressed his eagerness to cooperate with the new government.
title: UN nuclear watchdog extends congratulations, offers cooperation to Iran's new president

description: TEHRAN- Iran's acting Minister of Foreign Affairs has condemned Germany's decision to shut down the Islamic Center Hamburg (IZH), labeling the move as a boon for extremists, violent organizations, and groups that support terrorism globally.
title: Ban of Islamic Center Hamburg aids terrorism: acting FM

description: TEHRAN – On Thursday, the world looked on in shock as the U.S. Congress repeatedly stood for applause for Benjamin Netanyahu, the Israeli Prime Minister responsible for the deaths of over 40,000 Palestinians in the past ten months.
title: Bibi's lies and delusions

description: TEHRAN– Iran's permanent mission to the United Nations has dismissed Israeli claims that Resistance groups pose a threat to Israeli athletes and tourists at the Paris Olympic Games, labeling the allegations as "lies."
title: Iran denies Israeli claims of threats to athletes at Paris Olympics

description: TEHRAN– Iran has expressed strong approval for a China-mediated agreement aimed at mending the rift between Palestinian factions and establishing a national unity government, calling it a significant move towards reconciliation and consensus.
title: Tehran praises China-brokered agreement for Palestinian unity

description: TEHRAN – In a recent interview with the media outlet of the office of the Leader of Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Khamenei, President-elect Masoud Pezeshkian underscored the importance of adhering to the Leader’s general policies as a crucial factor in resolving disputes and fostering national unity.
title: Pezeshkian emphasizes unity through adherence to Leader’s policies

description: TEHRAN - In a note, the Iran newspaper addressed the shutting down of the Hamburg Islamic Center by the German government and wrote: The reason for Germany's recent action should be found in the good relations between the government of this country and anti-Iranian groups.
title: A vain hope for the fake opposition

description: TEHRAN- The commander of Army’s Ground Forces engineering group announced on Thursday the plan to close Iran's northeastern borders using four engineering groups from the army and the Khatam al-Anbiya construction headquarters.
title: Iran builds wall across eastern borders to boost security: commander

description: A group of 45 American doctors and nurses who have experience working in Gaza since October have written a letter to US President Joe Biden, First Lady Jill Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris recounting “the massive human toll from Israel’s attack” on the territory, Al Jazeera reported.
title: US medical workers: Gaza children ‘deliberately’ shot

description: TEHRAN- The Israeli prime minister addressed a joint session of the US Congress on Wednesday amid his army’s genocidal war on Gaza that has claimed the lives of more than 39,000 Palestinians over the past nine months.
title: Behind Bibi's web of deceit

description: TEHRAN- As Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu addressed the U.S. Congress, tens of thousands rallied outside the building, protesting against his visit and calling for an end to the Israeli genocidal war on Gaza.
title: Unwelcome guest in the Capitol

description: Protesters held up Palestinian and Yemeni flags and chanted slogans against the United States and Israel.
title: Yemenis rally in Sanaa in support of Gaza

description: British Prime Minister Keir Starmer will drop the UK's objection to an arrest warrant being issued by the International Criminal Court (ICC) for Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, saying it was a matter for the court.
title: UK dropping its objection to ICC arrest warrant for Netanyahu

description: PORTLAND - Most people have witnessed the unfolding Israeli horrors in Gaza. No sane human being could classify Israel’s war as self-defense. It is brutal carnage in real time. Israel has killed well over 40,000 Palestinians, including 30,000 women and children in Gaza, with many more likely buried under the rubble and thousands injured; it has denied food and basic medicine to suffering Palestinians who have had limbs amputated without anesthetic and who face imminent danger of starvation, cholera and polio; and it has displaced the entire population of Gaza several times over.
title: Could the Gaza war morph into a Muslim-Jewish war and entrap the United States?

description: TEHRAN-The 1988 Senegalese war-drama film “The Camp at Thiaroye” written and directed by Ousmane Sembène and Thierno Faty Sow will be screened at the cinematheque of the Tehran Museum of Contemporary Art (TMoCA) on Sunday.
title: TMoCA cinematheque to show Senegalese war-drama “The Camp at Thiaroye”

description:
* A collection of paintings by Mitra Ahmadi Avaz is currently on display in an exhibition at Ev Gallery. 
Entitled “Watching the Layers”, the exhibition runs until August 9 at the gallery located at No.5, Arabi Alley, North Kheradmand St., Karim Khan Ave.
title: What’s in Tehran art galleries

description: TEHRAN-The Persian translation of the novel “Their Eyes Were Watching God” by American writer Zora Neale Hurston has been released in the book market across Iran.
title: Zora Neale Hurston’s “Their Eyes Were Watching God” available in Persian

description: TEHRAN-The Iranian documentary “Destiny” by Yaser Talebi has won two awards at the 18th Faito Doc Festival, which was held from July 17 to 24 in Italy.
title: Iranian documentary “Destiny” grabs 2 prizes at Italy’s Faito Doc Festival

description: TEHRAN- With less than a month remaining for submissions to the 6th edition of the International Biennial Book Cartoon Contest, artists from 28 countries have already entered this prestigious festival.
title: 28 countries enter 6th Intl. Biennial Book Cartoon Contest

description: TEHRAN – Tens of international students hailing from some 50 countries, have explored Qazvin’s places of interest in a one-day tour.
title: Qazvin makes a big hit with intl. students

description: TEHRAN – As one of the most sought-after travel destinations across Iran, Gilan province has recorded some seven million overnight stays so far this summer, said a local tourism official.
title: Gilan registers 7 million overnight stays in month

description: TEHRAN – Iranian and Indian tourism officials have met to pave the way for enhanced bilateral cooperation in cultural heritage and tourism, marking a new chapter in the long-lasting relations between the two nations.
title: Iran, India seek stronger tourism ties

description: TEHRAN – Restoration work has commenced on the Muqarnas-shaped mirrorwork of a UNESCO-listed historical palace in downtown Tehran.
title: Exquisite mirrorwork of UNESCO-listed palace undergoes restoration

description: TEHRAN - The international tourism scene has shown a remarkable recovery after the COVID-19 pandemic. However, the story seems somewhat different when it comes to Iran.
title: Iran’s tourism shifts: former deputy minister shares insights

description: TEHRAN – Iranian sprinter Hassan Taftian met president of International Olympic Committee (IOC) Thomas Bach in the Olympic Village.
title: Hassan Taftian meets IOC President Thomas Bach

description: TEHRAN - Bayer Leverkusen have reportedly found a buyer for striker Sardar Azmoun.
title: Sardar Azmoun switches from Leverkusen to Dubai

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s Hamed Momeni has been appointed by FIFA to officiate at Paris Olympic 2024.
title: Iranian official appointed FIFA match coordinator in 2024 Olympics

description: TEHRAN – The head of Iran’s Securities and Exchange Organization (SEO) has said that the capital of the companies active in the stock market increased by 5.0 quadrillion rials (about $10 billion) in the previous Iranian calendar year (ended on March 19).
title: Capital of companies active in stock market rises by $10b in a year

description: The Archipelago 2024 project-educational intensive held on Sakhalin from July 8 to 21 drew the attention of the authorities and the public to the development of unmanned technologies. The goal of the Strategy for the Development of Unmanned Aviation in Russia up to 2030 is the establishment of a new economic sector in Russia associated with the manufacture and application of civilian drones. TV BRICS is an international media partner for the event.
title: The Archipelago 2024 project-educational intensive draws attention to unmanned technologies

description: TEHRAN –Following a recent agreement within the framework of the joint cooperation committee, Russia and Iran will establish a subcommittee for scientific and technological cooperation, Deputy Minister of Science and Higher Education of Russia Ayrat Gatiyatov has stated.
title: Tehran, Moscow to establish joint science, technology committee

description: TEHRAN -Iranian students have succeeded in grabbing two gold medals, and a specific award in the 13th World Invention Creativity Olympic (WICO) 2024.
title: Iranian teams grab gold medals in WICO 2024

description: TEHRAN - The International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies has released a report on the most important achievements of the Iranian Red Crescent Society during January-December 2023.
title: IFRC outlines achievements of Iranian Red Crescent Society

description: TEHRAN – Iran men’s goalball head coach Bahman Doosti Vala is optimistic about their chance of winning a medal in the 2024 Paralympic Games.
title: Iran men’s goalball aim for 2024 Paralympics medal, coach says

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s wheat production is expected to reach 15 million tons in the current crop year (September 2023-2024), an official with the Agriculture Ministry said.
title: Annual wheat production expected to reach 15m tons

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Trade Promotion Organization (TPO) has held a seminar on the trade opportunities of Iran and Turkmenistan as the Islamic Republic is going to hold specialized agrifood exhibition in Turkmenistan, the TPO portal reported.
title: TPO holds seminar on Iran-Turkmenistan trade opportunities

description: TEHRAN- As announced by the director general of the Iranian Ministry of Agriculture’s Office of Quality Improvement, Processing, and Aquatic Market, the country imported 13,972 tons of foods to breed fishery during the first quarter of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-June 20).
title: Nearly 14,000 tons of fish food imported in a quarter

description: TEHRAN- Iran exported over 100,000 tons of medicinal plants in the past Iranian calendar year (ended on March 19), Hossein Zeynali, the director of Agriculture Ministry’s medicinal plants national plan, announced.
title: Over 100,000 tons of medicinal plants exported in a year

description: TEHRAN - Iran exported about 2.226 million tons of agricultural products valued at $1.18 billion in the first four months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-July 21), registering an increase of 32 percent in value year on year.
title: Export of agricultural products up 32% in 4 months yr/yr
